conc([], L, L).
conc([H|T], L2, [H|R]) :-
    conc(T, L2, R).

revlist([], []).
revlist([H|T], R) :-
    revlist(T, R1),
    conc(R1, [H], R).

palindrome(L) :-
    revlist(L, R),
    L = R.


1. Maximum element in a list
Code (clean version)
max_list([X], X).
max_list([H|T], Max) :-
    max_list(T, MaxT),
    ( H > MaxT -> Max = H ; Max = MaxT ).

Example query
?- max_list([3,9,2,7], M).
M = 9.

ğŸ“Œ Explanation (very simple)

[H|T] means:

H = first element (Head)

T = remaining list (Tail)

Base case
max_list([X], X).


ğŸ‘‰ If the list has only one element, that element is the maximum.

Recursive case
max_list([H|T], Max) :-
    max_list(T, MaxT),
    ( H > MaxT -> Max = H ; Max = MaxT ).


Steps:

Find maximum of the tail â†’ MaxT

Compare H and MaxT

Bigger one becomes Max

ğŸ”¹ 2. Print numbers from N down to 1
Code
print_down(0).
print_down(N) :-
    N > 0,
    write(N), nl,
    N1 is N - 1,
    print_down(N1).

Example
?- print_down(5).
5
4
3
2
1
true.

ğŸ“Œ Explanation

write(N) â†’ prints number

nl â†’ new line

is â†’ evaluates arithmetic

Base case
print_down(0).


ğŸ‘‰ Stop when number becomes 0

Recursive case
print_down(N) :-
    N > 0,
    write(N),
    N1 is N - 1,
    print_down(N1).


ğŸ‘‰ Prints N, then calls itself with N-1

ğŸ”¹ 3. Count occurrences of an element in a list
Code
count(_, [], 0).

count(X, [X|T], N) :-
    count(X, T, N1),
    N is N1 + 1.

count(X, [_|T], N) :-
    count(X, T, N).

Example
?- count(1, [1,2,4,1,3,5,0,1,2,5,1], N).
N = 4.

ğŸ“Œ Explanation

We want to count how many times X appears.

Base case
count(_, [], 0).


ğŸ‘‰ Empty list â†’ count is 0

Case 1: Head equals X
count(X, [X|T], N) :-
    count(X, T, N1),
    N is N1 + 1.


ğŸ‘‰ Found one occurrence â†’ add 1

Case 2: Head is NOT X
count(X, [_|T], N) :-
    count(X, T, N).


ğŸ‘‰ Ignore head, continue

ğŸ”¹ 4. Length of a list
Code
list_length([], 0).

list_length([_|T], N) :-
    list_length(T, N1),
    N is N1 + 1.

Example
?- list_length([1,5,7,9,3,6,4], L).
L = 7.

ğŸ“Œ Explanation
Base case
list_length([], 0).


ğŸ‘‰ Empty list has length 0

Recursive case
list_length([_|T], N) :-
    list_length(T, N1),
    N is N1 + 1.


_ means â€œI donâ€™t care about this valueâ€

Count tail length

Add 1 for current element
